Bet9ja Nigeria National League side, Osun United Football Club, technical crew and management has taken a giant step towards ensuring they restart the NNL on a high note having concluded plans to boost their squad with new exceptional players. Coach Duke Udi, took a giant step having strengthened his squad as he attempt to rescue the Omoluabi Giants from relegation.
Top among the newly recruited players is former Flying Eagles defender Suraj Sodiq, and former Niger Tornadoes midfielder, George James. Others include Sunday Afolabi from Rivers United, Ogini Olatunbosun from Shooting Stars, Mojeed Yusuf, and the trio of Chinedu Emmanuel, Adeyemi Olasupo, and Alaji Rasaq from Ikorodu United.